laboratory_examinations.procedure_name: LH and FSH response to pulsatile GnRH administration
laboratory_examinations.findings: At 75 ng/kg: LH 0.31 IU/liter, FSH 24 IU/liter; At 100 ng/kg: LH 0.42 IU/liter, FSH 13 IU/liter; At 150 ng/kg: Peak estradiol 256 pg/ml; At 250 ng/kg: LH 0.53 IU/liter; At 500 ng/kg: LH 0.64 IU/liter, Peak estradiol 126 pg/ml.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: Increase in LH and FSH responses was observed at increased doses of GnRH, but LH levels remained low compared to IHH controls.
